31
00:02:33,656 --&gt; 00:02:36,417
compared to the understanding of the toxicity of medicine by modern medical field

32
00:02:36,699 --&gt; 00:02:38,989
But with the development of theory of property of medicine in Chinese Traditional Medicine

33
00:02:39,271 --&gt; 00:02:44,469
such as the knowledge of warmness, heat coldness and coldness and the knowledge of the ascending descending floating and sinking as we mentioned just now

34
00:02:45,175 --&gt; 00:02:49,246
people's understanding of the toxicity of medicine gradually entered the broad sense of toxicity

35
00:02:49,527 --&gt; 00:02:54,160
that is the deviation of the medicine (towards warm or cool) and there is little medicine which is absolutely flat in property. 

36
00:02:54,441 --&gt; 00:03:01,885
So it will be reasonable to account for the toxicity of medicine according to its degree of deviation.

37
00:03:02,163 --&gt; 00:03:03,989
for an example,

38
00:03:04,319 --&gt; 00:03:09,699
It was once reported that Ginseng and Rhizoma Anemarrhenae were also resulted in poisonous reaction even they were once considered as non-toxic.

39
00:03:09,935 --&gt; 00:03:13,490
It was because the dosage was excessive 

40
